Authors : James Cuff and Michele Clamp 2011
-------------------------------------------

Description
------------

JAuth is a reference desktop client for the google authenticator. 
Intended as an alternative to the iPhone Google Authenticator app and similar.

http://code.google.com/p/google-authenticator/

Demo
----

http://minilims.bioteam.net/JAuth.demo.jnlp

(Uses a dummy secret key - usually this would be in a .google_authenticator file on your local system)

Installation
------------

To compile and run in bash

./makejar

then to run 

java -jar JAuth.jar

or

java -jar JAuth.jar <myauthfile>

By default it looks in the current directory for a file called .google_authenticator

